sses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20I%20had%20really%20taken%20the%20Chicago%20School%20libertarian%20economic%20thinking%20to%20heart.%20I%20felt%20that%20all%20trade%20was%20good%20trade%2C%20and%20that%20moving%20manufacturing%20overseas%20was%20what%20you%20did%2C%20and%20made%20financial%20sense%2C%20so%20I%20followed%20that%20script.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20what%20began%20to%20dawn%20on%20me%20is%20that%20I%20was%20becoming%20increasingly%20disconnected%20from%20the%20product%20that%20I%20was%20selling%2C%20and%20I%20really%20hated%20that%20feeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20hated%20that%20I%20would%20work%20with%20these%20people%20that%20helped%20me%20stand%20the%20business%20up%20and%20then%2C%20because%20I%20could%20get%20a%20part%20that%20was%20stamped%20for%2010%20or%2015%20or%2020%20cents%20cheaper%2C%20I%20could%20cut%20my%20labor%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20had%20my%20first%20daughter%20in%202010%2C%20I%20just%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20it%20anymore.%20I%20got%20this%20pretty%20naive%20notion%20to%20start%20American%20Giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%2070s%20and%2080s%20with%20the%20great%20American%20clothing%20brands%20like%20Levi's%20and%20Wrangler%20and%20Champion%20and%20Red%20Wing%20and%20Woolrich.%20Not%20only%20did%20they%20make%20the%20best%20products%20and%20clothing%20in%20the%20world%2C%20but%20I%20also%20felt%20that%20they%20said%20something%20about%20me%20when%20I%20wore%20them.%20They%20were%20substantive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202010%2C%20there%20were%20no%20clothing%20brands%20like%20that%20anymore.%20They'd%20all%20shipped%20overseas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20launched%20with%20a%20men's%20sweatshirt%2C%20because%20I%20was%20just%20interested%20in%20that%20category%2C%20and%20a%20news%20article%20called%20it%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Ftechnology%2F2012%2F12%2Famerican-giant-hoodie-this-is-the-greatest-sweatshirt-known-to-man.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20grea